    <td valign="middle"><h2 align="center"><a href="/web/20170903031504/http://www.osb.org/osbsitemap.html">The Order of Saint
    Benedict</a></h2>
    <h3 align="center">The Congregations and Federations <br>
	of North America</h3></td>
  </tr>
</table>

<p>&nbsp;</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Most of the North American houses of Benedictine men and women are listed below, with their
  affiliation to the several federations or congregations, and their European origins are noted
  in capitals. In the main, the congregations tend to represent the same European origin,
  though there are a few exceptions. The different indentations in the listing are meant to
  indicate the &quot;generation&quot; or stage of removal of the federation from the European source.</p>
</blockquote>

<table cellpadding="5" width="100%" align="left" style="border-collapse: collapse" bordercolor="#111111" cellspacing="0"> 
